<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-49-0105 </DOCNO><TEXT>A survey of VDEW member companies shows that the German power economyis intensively and extensively engaged in harnessing wind and solar energiesfor electricity generation. Consequently, the power economy is makingan important contribution to testing and developing these technologies,which even today can be used with economical benefits in areas lackinga supply of power. This opens up for German companies with demonstrationprojects export oppurtunities to developing nations, where it may beotherwise necessary to import primary energy at high transport costs.As yet, it is impossible to say when industrialized countries will beable to economically supply to the public grid from wind an sun withoutadditional subsidies. However, the electricity economy is opening upthese options for the future.</TEXT></DOC>